definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + a quinone -eq- glycerone phosphate + a quinol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + O(2) -eq- glycerone phosphate + H(2)O(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + glycerol -eq- sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + glycerone -eq- ADP + glycerone phosphate + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + glycine + H2O -eq- tetrahydrofolate + L-serine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) -eq- UDP + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction -  glycine + lipoylprotein -eq- S-aminomethyldihydrolipoylprotein + CO2.
Catalysis of the transfer of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue from GDP-mannose into lipid-linked oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-D-mannosyl-D-mannose linkage.

Catalysis of the reaction -  an alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + 2 GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- an alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + 2 GDP + 2 H+. This reaction is the transfer of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue from GDP-mannose into lipid-linked oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-2)-D-mannosyl-D-mannose linkage.

Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-3)-beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + GDP + H+. This reaction is the transfer of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue from GDP-mannose into lipid-linked oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-3)-D-mannosyl-D-mannose linkage.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tetradecanoyl-CoA + glycyl-peptide -eq- CoA + N-tetradecanoylglycyl-peptide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + glycoprotein-alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2)-D-galactose -eq- UDP + glycoprotein-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1,3)-(alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2))-D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-galactose + glycoprotein-alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2)-D-galactose -eq- UDP + glycoprotein-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1,3)-(alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2))-D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP + H2O -eq- GMP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP -eq- 3',5'-cyclic GMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + GMP -eq- ADP + GDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NTP + H2O -eq- NDP + phosphate, to drive the unwinding of a DNA or RNA helix.
Catalysis of the reaction -  heme + 3 donor-H2 + 3 O2 -eq- biliverdin + Fe2+ + CO + 3 acceptor + 3 H2O.

Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + heparan sulfate -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + heparan sulfate 2-O-sulfate -  results in 2-O-sulfation of iduronic acid residues in heparan sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 3-hexaprenyl-4,5-dihydroxybenzoate -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 3-hexaprenyl-4-hydroxy-5-methoxybenzoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-hexose -eq- ADP + D-hexose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-histidine -eq- urocanate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-histidine -eq- histamine + CO2.

Catalysis of the reaction -  L-histidinol-phosphate + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- 3-(imidazol-4-yl)-2-oxopropyl phosphate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-histidinol phosphate + H(2)O -eq- L-histidinol + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + histone -eq- CoA + acetyl-histone.

Catalysis of the reaction -  histone N6-acetyl-L-lysine + H2O -eq- histone L-lysine + acetate. This reaction represents the removal of an acetyl group from a histone, a class of proteins complexed to DNA in chromatin and chromosomes.
Catalysis of the reaction -  holocytochrome c -eq- apocytochrome c + heme.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (-)-homoisocitrate -eq- cis-homoaconitate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + acetyl-CoA + H(2)O -eq- CoA + H(+) + homocitrate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  L-homoserine + acetyl-CoA -eq- O-acetyl-L-homoserine + CoA.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-4) linkages between N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and D-glucuronate residues in hyaluronate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-mevalonate + CoA + 2 NADP(+) -eq- (S)-3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl-CoA + 2 H(+) + 2 NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetoacetyl-CoA + acetyl-CoA + H(2)O -eq- (S)-3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl-CoA + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  IMP + diphosphate -eq- hypoxanthine + 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 2-sulfate groups of the L-iduronate 2-sulfate units of dermatan sulfate, heparan sulfate and heparin.

Catalysis of the reaction -  diphosphate + H(2)O -eq- H(+) + 2 phosphate.
